                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.113/9155</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Ambassador <persName type="from">Fletcher</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Extract]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-09-11T23:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 11, 1917, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>432. President Carranza informs me that General Gonzalez has telegraphed him from
                    Laredo that all cartridges released by us have been sent from San Antonio to
                    Laredo. He therefore requests that appropriate orders be given authorities at
                    Laredo to pass entire consignment and it will be cheaper and more convenient to
                    receive them all at Laredo and make distribution from this side than to follow
                    arrangement originally provisioned in my 357.<note n="2" xml:id="d1313fn2">Not
                        printed.</note> Please reply.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fletcher</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
